Hello, This proposal comes from an action item received at the 28 July teleconf [1]. 
In the 16 July revision of the UAGL [2], checkpoint 9.9 reads: 9.9 Make available the primary language of a document's content. 
[Priority 3] For example, use HTTP header information or language attribute information from the document root. 
Proposed change (Priority 1, for assistive techologies): Render content according to natural language changes identified by markup. 
For unsupported natural languages, allow the user request prompting when language changes. 
NOTES: a) This checkpoint is meant to cover checkpoints 4.1 and 4.3 from WCAG 1.0: both primary language and language changes. 
Note that since 4.1 is priority 1, this one is too. 
b) This checkpoint is also meant to allow users to turn on/off support for alerts to language changes. 
