It is merely a question of conformance. 
Any piece of software may claim conformance as an assisitive technology, which means that it satisfies a subset of the checkpoints. 
If HPR wishes to claim that type of conformance, it must satisfy that checkpoint. 
The question remains: are the two categories useful and will it make sense for software we are familiar with to conform to one category or the other? 
